{"questionId":"13890","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The first terms of an infinite geometric sequence,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{u_n}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>u</mi>\n      <mi>n</mi>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>, are 2, 6, 18, 54, …</p>\n<p>The first terms of a second infinite geometric sequence, <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{v_n}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>v</mi>\n      <mi>n</mi>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>, are&nbsp;2, −6, 18, −54, …</p>\n<p>The terms of a third sequence, <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{w_n}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>w</mi>\n      <mi>n</mi>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>, are defined as&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{w_n} = {u_n} + {v_n}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>w</mi>\n      <mi>n</mi>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>u</mi>\n      <mi>n</mi>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>v</mi>\n      <mi>n</mi>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The finite series,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\sum\\limits_{k = 1}^{225} {{w_k}} \">\n  <munderover>\n    <mo movablelimits=\"false\">∑</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>k</mi>\n      <mo>=</mo>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>225</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </munderover>\n  <mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <msub>\n        <mi>w</mi>\n        <mi>k</mi>\n      </msub>\n    </mrow>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> ,&nbsp;can also be written in the form <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\sum\\limits_{k = 0}^m {4{r^k}} \">\n  <munderover>\n    <mo movablelimits=\"false\">∑</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>k</mi>\n      <mo>=</mo>\n      <mn>0</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mi>m</mi>\n  </munderover>\n  <mrow>\n    <mn>4</mn>\n    <mrow>\n      <msup>\n        <mi>r</mi>\n        <mi>k</mi>\n      </msup>\n    </mrow>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the value&nbsp;of&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"r\"> <mi>r</mi> </math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>valid approach &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em>eg</em>&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"4 \\times {r^1} = 36\"> <mn>4</mn> <mo>×</mo> <mrow> <msup> <mi>r</mi> <mn>1</mn> </msup> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mn>36</mn> </math></span>,&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"4 \\times {9^{n - 1}}\"> <mn>4</mn> <mo>×</mo> <mrow> <msup> <mn>9</mn> <mrow> <mi>n</mi> <mo>−</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> </msup> </mrow> </math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"r = 9\"> <mi>r</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mn>9</mn> </math></span>&nbsp; (accept&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\sum\\limits_{k = 0}^m {4 \\times {9^k}} \"> <munderover> <mo movablelimits=\"false\">∑</mo> <mrow> <mi>k</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mn>0</mn> </mrow> <mi>m</mi> </munderover> <mrow> <mn>4</mn> <mo>×</mo> <mrow> <msup> <mn>9</mn> <mi>k</mi> </msup> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span>;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"m\"> <mi>m</mi> </math></span>&nbsp;may be incorrect) &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;A1 N2</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13890","referenceCode":"19M.2.SL.TZ1.S_7b.i","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the value of r .","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.2—Arithmetic sequences and series"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}